This paper discusses the application of deep neural networks (DNNs) to various machine learning tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the use of rectified-linear-unit (ReLU) activations, which is a common technique in neural networks for computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of the Adam optimizer, which is a popular optimization algorithm in neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of model size, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
